#%fig=pyplot
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt #

x = np.linspace(0, 10, 1000)
y = np.sin(x)
z = np.cos(x**2)

plt.figure(figsize=(8,4)) #

plt.plot(x,y,label="$sin(x)$",color="red",linewidth=2) #
plt.plot(x,z,"b--",label="$cos(x^2)$") #

plt.xlabel("Time(s)") #
plt.ylabel("Volt") 
plt.title("PyPlot First Example") 
plt.ylim(-1.2,1.2) 
plt.legend() 

plt.show() #

In [30]:
#%fig[1x2]=
plt.figure(1) # 1
plt.figure(2) # 2
ax1 = plt.subplot(121) # 21
ax2 = plt.subplot(122) # 22

x = np.linspace(0, 3, 100)
for i in range(5):
    plt.figure(1)  # 1
    plt.plot(x, np.exp(i*x/3))
    plt.sca(ax1)   # 21
    plt.plot(x, np.sin(i*x))
    plt.sca(ax2)  # 22
    plt.plot(x, np.cos(i*x))

ax3 = plt.subplot2grid((3, 3), (1, 0), rowspan=2)
ax4 = plt.subplot2grid((3, 3), (2, 1), colspan=2)

    ax.text(0.5, 0.5, "ax{}".format(idx), ha="center", va="center", fontsize=16)

y = np.sin(x)
z = np.cos(x**2)

plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))

plt.plot(x,y,label="$sin(x)$",linewidth=2)
plt.plot(x,z,"--",label="$cos(x^2)$")

plt.xlabel("Time(s)")
plt.ylabel("Volt") 
plt.title("ggplot style") 
plt.ylim(-1.2,1.2) 
plt.legend();

In [18]:
#%fig=
import os
from os import path

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 7))
ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
plt.subplots_adjust(0, 0, 1, 1, 0, 0)
plt.xticks([])
plt.yticks([])
x, y = 0.05, 0.05
fonts = [font.name for font in fontManager.ttflist if 
             path.exists(font.fname) and os.stat(font.fname).st_size>1e6] #
font = set(fonts)
dy = (1.0 - y) / (len(fonts) // 4 + (len(fonts)%4 != 0))

for font in fonts:
    t = ax.text(x, y + dy / 2, "", 
                {'fontname':font, 'fontsize':14}, transform=ax.transAxes) #
    ax.text(x, y, font, {'fontsize':12}, transform=ax.transAxes)
    x += 0.25
    if x >= 1.0:
        y += dy
        x = 0.05
plt.show()
